  "prompt": "What do Flipkart's delivery guys look for when I exchange my old phone for a new one?",
  "response": "When exchanging your old phone for a new one on Flipkart (or similar platforms), the delivery personnel typically look for several key factors to assess the condition of the old device:\n\n1. **Physical Condition**: They will check for obvious signs of wear and tear, such as scratches, dents, cracks, and overall appearance. A phone in good condition generally fetches a better exchange value.\n\n2. **Functionality**: The delivery person may verify whether the phone powers on and functions properly. This includes checking the touchscreen responsiveness, camera functionality, and general performance.\n\n3. **Battery Health**: The battery health is an important factor. If the phone has a severely degraded battery, it may not be accepted or could lower the exchange value.\n\n4. **Accessories**: Availability of original accessories like chargers, earphones, and boxes can also impact the exchange value. Having these accessories can sometimes lead to a better assessment.\n\n5. **Water and Liquid Damage**: Many phones have indicators that show if the device has sustained water damage. They may look for signs of this damage, which could influence their decision.\n\n6. **Unlock Status**: The phone is ideally expected to be unlocked from any carrier, which can affect whether they accept the exchange.\n\n7. **IMEI and Serial Number**: They may check the IMEI and serial number to verify the model and its eligibility for exchange.\n\n8. **Cleanliness**: While this may not impact the functionality, a clean device may positively influence the assessment.\n\nIf you're considering exchanging your old phone, it's good to ensure it's clean, in good working condition, and, if possible, free from personal data or accounts (like factory resetting it) to streamline the process.",
